CustomAutoindex made for generating html of directory contents.

usage:

	./custom_autoindex --tree|-t|--serve|-s|--single|-s <directory>

-t, --tree - make full tree starting from <directory> and write it to tree.html.
-s, --serve - start http server under 8080 port. Server generates one level html upon request and responds with it.
              Only GET allowed.
-S, --single - prints one level html to stdout.

header.html and footer.html are requred in executable directory for correct workflow.
.html files are customizable.
